 real job training or needed childcare options, ultimately causing many families to fall deeper below the poverty line.Not Working shows that the new “welfare-to-work” regime has produced tremendous instability and insecurity for these women and their children. Moreover, the authors argue that the new politics of welfare enable greater infringements of rights and liberty for many of America's most vulnerable and constitute a crucial component of the broader assault on American citizenship. In short, the new welfare is not working.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aImmigrantszCaliforniazLong BeachxEconomic conditions. 0aImmigrantszCaliforniazLong BeachxSocial conditions. 0aMexican American womenzCaliforniazLong BeachxEconomic conditions. 0aMexican American womenzCaliforniazLong BeachxSocial conditions. 0aPublic welfarexPolitical aspectszUnited States. 0aWelfare recipientsxEmploymentzUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Discrimination & Race Relations.2bisacsh  a1996.  aChronicles.  adevastating.  aeffects.  aended.  aknow.  alegislation.  areform.  athat.  awelfare.1 aTheoharis, Jeanne, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831107064440 cprintz978081475709340uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9780814761311.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814761311423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780814761311/original  a978-3-11-070644-4  New York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK